RFC USNChat01 — Simple Educational Chat Protocol (SECP)
Status of This Memo
This memo defines an experimental communication protocol intended for educational use.
Distribution of this memo is unlimited.
Abstract
This document specifies the Simple Educational Chat Protocol (SECP), a lightweight chat
protocol designed for students learning network programming. SECP intentionally combines
UDP and TCP to demonstrate broadcast, multicast, unicast, and reliable connections. The
protocol supports open and closed chat rooms, guaranteed delivery rooms using TCP, and
optional encrypted communication for private guaranteed rooms.
